{#-
  instruction.jinja (English)
  Minimal per-request instruction line.
  scenario_enabled=True: assumes the performer draws on the reference scripts.
  scenario_enabled=False (ablation): drops all "reference script" mentions and
  asks the LLM to play the character directly.
  Expects: request_key, info (optional), scenario_enabled?
-#}
{%- set _scenario_enabled = scenario_enabled if scenario_enabled is defined else False -%}
{% if request_key == 'talk' -%}
{%- set _self_talk_today = talk_history | selectattr('agent', 'equalto', info.agent) | selectattr('day', 'equalto', info.day) | list | length -%}
{% if _scenario_enabled -%}
Day {{ info.day }} talk.{% if _self_talk_today == 0 %} This is your first utterance today.{% endif %} Draw on the discussion flow and utterance tempo of the reference scripts, and speak naturally as your character. Do not imitate the format — output your utterance content only.
{%- else -%}
Day {{ info.day }} talk.{% if _self_talk_today == 0 %} This is your first utterance today.{% endif %} Speak naturally as your character. Output your utterance content only — no headings, tables, character labels, voiced others, or stage directions.
{%- endif %}
{% elif request_key == 'whisper' -%}
Day {{ info.day }} whisper. Reply to your fellow werewolf naturally, staying in character.
{% elif request_key == 'divine' -%}
Divine request. Output only the name of the agent to divine.
{% elif request_key == 'guard' -%}
Guard request. Output only the name of the agent to guard.
{% elif request_key == 'vote' -%}
Vote request. You are "{{ info.agent }}". Considering the stance and declarations you yourself have publicly stated in the discussion (e.g. "I vote for @X"), any divination results you have received, and other agents' COs and claims, choose the most consistent execution-vote target. **Do not vote for yourself ("{{ info.agent }}") unless you have a specific reason to.** You do not need to follow the majority's vote declarations — stay consistent with your own stance and reasoning. Output only the target agent name with no additional characters.
{% elif request_key == 'attack' -%}
Attack request. Output only the name of the agent to attack.
{% elif request_key == 'initialize' -%}
{%- set _primer %}Divination and medium results are facts the server returns; the result itself has no "reason", so when judging whether a claimed seer is fake, weigh the choice of divine target, the consistency of that seer's words and conduct, and cross-checks against others' statements (questioning the basis of the result itself is beside the point). A common flow: with a single seer claim (1-CO), generally treat that seer as genuine and move promptly to the execution-vote discussion; with two or more claims (2+ CO), weigh the target-selection reasoning to judge which is genuine, then move to the vote discussion. If you hold an information role (seer/medium), come out (CO) and share your result at an appropriate time so the village can act on it.{% endset -%}
{% if _scenario_enabled -%}
Game initialize. Using the reference scripts you studied and the role/profile that follows, respond in English to subsequent requests. {{ _primer | trim }}
{%- else -%}
Game initialize. Using the role/profile that follows, respond in English to subsequent requests. {{ _primer | trim }}
{%- endif %}
{% elif request_key == 'daily_initialize' -%}
Day {{ info.day }} has started.
{% elif request_key == 'daily_finish' -%}
Day {{ info.day }} has ended.
{% endif -%}
